Author:
Vol / Page:
Edition:
Quote:  <i>Karitane, </i>a Plunket nurse, trained member of the Plunket Society, the Royal New Zealand Society for the Health of Women and Children, founded by Sir Truby King in 1907 at his Karitane home near Dunedin. (He called his society after the then Governor General.)
